---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Contract-Driven Development — Eidos AGI"
  description="Agents execute specs, not vibes. Every decision has a confidence level. Every action traces back to a contract."
>
  <div class="page">
    <div class="mark">
      <a href="/">eidos agi</a>
      <div class="mark-right">
        <nav id="nav-menu">
          <a href="https://github.com/eidos-agi">github</a>
          <a href="https://pypi.org/user/eidos-agi/">pypi</a>
        </nav>
        <button class="hamburger" id="hamburger" aria-label="Menu" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="nav-menu">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <line x1="3" y1="5" x2="17" y2="5"/>
            <line x1="3" y1="10" x2="17" y2="10"/>
            <line x1="3" y1="15" x2="17" y2="15"/>
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <article class="cdd-page">
      <header class="cdd-hero">
        <h1>Contract-Driven<br />Development</h1>
        <p class="cdd-sub">Agents execute specs, not vibes.</p>
      </header>

      <section class="cdd-section">
        <h2>The problem</h2>
        <p>When an AI agent runs a task, it makes decisions. Which approach to use, what to prioritize, when to stop. Most of those decisions happen in conversation — unrecorded, unreviewable, unreproducible. The agent improvises. Sometimes it improvises well. Sometimes it doesn't. Either way, there's no receipt.</p>
        <p>Contract-driven development replaces improvisation with specification. Every decision has a confidence level. Every action traces back to a contract. Nothing runs on "inferred" — it runs on "proven."</p>
      </section>

      <section class="cdd-section">
        <h2>The confidence model</h2>
        <p>Every fact an agent depends on carries a confidence level:</p>
        <table class="cdd-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Level</th>
              <th>Meaning</th>
              <th>Can build on?</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="cdd-level cdd-proven">proven</td>
              <td>Tested in production, confirmed working</td>
              <td>Yes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="cdd-level cdd-tested">tested</td>
              <td>Validated against real system, not yet production</td>
              <td>Yes, with monitoring</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="cdd-level cdd-researched">researched</td>
              <td>From documentation, not verified</td>
              <td>Verify first</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="cdd-level cdd-inferred">inferred</td>
              <td>Guessed from similar systems</td>
              <td>No — must verify</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="cdd-level cdd-unknown">unknown</td>
              <td>No information available</td>
              <td>No — must discover</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="cdd-level cdd-blocked">blocked</td>
              <td>Known to exist but can't verify</td>
              <td>No — must unblock</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>The readiness of a system is the lowest confidence level of its constituent parts. One "unknown" field means the system is not production-ready, even if 99% of fields are proven.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="cdd-section">
        <h2>The trilogy implements it</h2>
        <div class="cdd-trio">
          <div class="cdd-trio-item">
            <h3>visionlog</h3>
            <p>Records the contracts — guardrails, goals, ADRs. These are the constraints all execution must honor. If an agent would violate a guardrail, the answer is already no.</p>
            <code>pip install visionlog-md</code>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-trio-item">
            <h3>research.md</h3>
            <p>Earns the decisions with evidence. Candidates are scored against locked criteria. Confidence levels are recorded. The research is the receipt.</p>
            <code>pip install research-md</code>
          </div>
          <div class="cdd-trio-item">
            <h3>ike.md</h3>
            <p>Executes tasks within the contracts. Every task links to the goal it serves and the decision that authorized the approach. Definition of Done is explicit, not assumed.</p>
            <code>pip install ike-md</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="cdd-section">
        <h2>What changes</h2>
        <div class="cdd-changes">
          <div>
            <h3>Without contracts</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Agent picks an approach based on training data</li>
              <li>Decisions happen in conversation, lost after session</li>
              <li>No one knows why a choice was made</li>
              <li>"It worked" is the only success criterion</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>With contracts</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Agent reads guardrails before acting</li>
              <li>Decisions are scored, recorded, reviewable</li>
              <li>Every choice traces to evidence</li>
              <li>Definition of Done is explicit and auditable</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="cdd-section">
        <p class="cdd-closing">Contract-driven development isn't a methodology to learn. It's three pip installs and a commitment to recording what matters. The agents do the work. The contracts make sure the work is trustworthy.</p>
        <pre><code>pip install visionlog-md research-md ike-md</code></pre>
      </section>
    </article>

    <footer class="foot">
      <span>&copy; {new Date().getFullYear()} Eidos AGI</span>
    </footer>
  </div>

  <script>
    const hb = document.getElementById('hamburger');
    const nm = document.getElementById('nav-menu');
    if (hb && nm) {
      hb.addEventListener('click', () => {
        nm.classList.toggle('open');
        hb.setAttribute('aria-expanded', nm.classList.contains('open'));
      });
      document.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
        if (!hb.contains(e.target) && !nm.contains(e.target)) nm.classList.remove('open');
      });
    }
  </script>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .cdd-page {
    max-width: var(--measure-prose);
  }

  .cdd-hero {
    padding: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-8);
  }
  .cdd-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, var(--text-4xl));
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .cdd-sub {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .cdd-section {
    padding: var(--space-12) 0;
    border-top: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 15%, transparent);
  }
  .cdd-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .cdd-section p {
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .cdd-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
  }
  .cdd-table th {
    text-align: left;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
    border-bottom: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent);
  }
  .cdd-table td {
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
    border-bottom: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 10%, transparent);
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }
  .cdd-level {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: var(--weight-medium);
  }
  .cdd-proven { color: var(--color-command); }
  .cdd-tested { color: var(--color-secondary); }
  .cdd-researched { color: var(--color-primary); }
  .cdd-inferred { color: var(--color-muted); }
  .cdd-unknown { color: var(--color-danger); }
  .cdd-blocked { color: var(--color-danger); }

  .cdd-trio {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }
  .cdd-trio-item {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }
  .cdd-trio-item h3 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .cdd-trio-item p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .cdd-trio-item code {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-command);
  }

  .cdd-changes {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }
  .cdd-changes h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .cdd-changes ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .cdd-changes li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    padding: var(--space-2) 0;
    border-bottom: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 8%, transparent);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }

  .cdd-closing {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cdd-trio { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .cdd-changes { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .cdd-table { font-size: var(--text-xs); }
  }
</style>
